oc:kn_09ea7b59 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Core DCF formulas for WACC, terminal value, and present value" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "plaintext" ;
    oc:directiveContent """WACC = (E/V × Cost of Equity) + (D/V × Cost of Debt × (1 - Tax Rate))
Cost of Equity = Risk-Free Rate + Beta × Equity Risk Premium
Terminal Value (Perpetuity) = FCF_final × (1 + g) / (WACC - g)
Terminal Value (Exit Multiple) = EBITDA_final × Exit Multiple
PV = Σ [FCFt / (1 + WACC)^t] + [TV / (1 + WACC)^n]""" .

oc:kn_0c2f1f7c a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When calculating unlevered free cash flow in DCF" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "plaintext" ;
    oc:directiveContent """EBIT
× (1 - Tax Rate)
= NOPAT
+ Depreciation & Amortization
- Capital Expenditures
- Increase in Net Working Capital
= Unlevered Free Cash Flow (UFCF)""" .

oc:kn_43bd069e a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When reconciling multiple valuation methodologies into a single price target" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Typical valuation weighting: DCF 40-60%, Trading Comps 25-40%, Precedent Transactions 15-25%. Adjust based on forecast confidence, market conditions, M&A likelihood, and company maturity." ;
    oc:hasRationale "No single method is definitive; weighting reflects relative reliability given context" .

oc:kn_47d15236 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When selecting valuation multiples for trading comps" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use EV/Revenue for high-growth/unprofitable companies, EV/EBITDA for capital-intensive industries, P/E for stable profitable companies, P/B for banks, EV/Production for oil & gas, EV/Subscriber for media." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Different multiples capture different aspects of value; using the wrong multiple produces misleading comparisons" .

oc:kn_5d1f8bcf a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before finalizing any valuation recommendation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Cross-check final valuation with: historical multiples consistency, peer comparison justification, implied growth rate market is pricing in, IRR from current to target price, and market cap reasonableness." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Sanity checks catch mathematical errors and unsupported assumptions before publication" .

oc:kn_74b9d07e a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When presenting valuation reconciliation summary" ;
    oc:directiveContent """| Method | Enterprise Value | Equity Value | Price/Share | Weight | Implied Value |
|--------|------------------|--------------|-------------|--------|---------------|
| DCF Analysis | {ev_dcf} | {eq_dcf} | {pps_dcf} | {w_dcf}% | {iv_dcf} |
| Trading Comps | {ev_comp} | {eq_comp} | {pps_comp} | {w_comp}% | {iv_comp} |
| Precedent Trans. | {ev_prec} | {eq_prec} | {pps_prec} | {w_prec}% | {iv_prec} |
| **Weighted Avg** | - | - | **{target_price}** | - | **{target_price}** |""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "eq_comp",
        "eq_dcf",
        "eq_prec",
        "ev_comp",
        "ev_dcf",
        "ev_prec",
        "iv_comp",
        "iv_dcf",
        "iv_prec",
        "pps_comp",
        "pps_dcf",
        "pps_prec",
        "target_price",
        "w_comp",
        "w_dcf",
        "w_prec" .

oc:kn_89c4a062 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When performing precedent transactions analysis" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Identify 5-10 relevant M&A transactions (same industry, 0.5x-2x target size, last 3-5 years) → 2. Gather transaction details from SEC filings, databases → 3. Calculate transaction multiples and control premium → 4. Build precedent table → 5. Apply to target, adjust for market conditions and deal context" ;
    oc:stepOrder 3 .

oc:kn_967e917a a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When presenting valuation conclusions" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always present a valuation range (Bear/Base/Bull cases) rather than a point estimate. Always perform sensitivity analysis on WACC vs terminal growth rate at minimum." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Point estimates create false precision; ranges communicate uncertainty and support defensible recommendations" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_b01f2c7d a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building DCF models" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never double-count growth by projecting high revenue growth without corresponding CapEx and NWC investment. Never use terminal growth rates exceeding long-term GDP growth (typically cap at 2-3%). Never use net income instead of unlevered FCF in a DCF." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These errors produce materially overstated valuations and undermine analytical credibility" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_b47eba3e a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When performing trading comparables analysis" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Select 5-10 comparable companies (same industry, similar size/growth/margins) → 2. Gather financials (stock price, LTM/NTM estimates) → 3. Calculate EV and equity multiples → 4. Build comps table, remove outliers >2σ → 5. Apply median multiple to target → 6. Bridge EV to price per share" ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

oc:kn_bb4a8e6b a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When applying precedent transaction multiples" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Precedent transaction multiples are typically higher than trading comps because they include control premiums (typically 20-40%). Weight recent transactions more heavily. Adjust for market conditions at transaction time vs. current conditions." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Control premiums and strategic synergies inflate transaction multiples relative to public market trading levels" .

oc:kn_dd8c113c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When performing DCF analysis" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Collect 3-5 years historical financials → 2. Build 5-10 year revenue projections (top-down or bottom-up) → 3. Project operating expenses → 4. Calculate UFCF (EBIT×(1-T) + D&A - CapEx - ΔNWC) → 5. Determine terminal value (perpetuity growth or exit multiple) → 6. Calculate WACC → 7. Discount to PV → 8. Bridge from EV to equity value per share → 9. Sensitivity analysis" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

